Sentencas: To illustrate the effect of Cu-doping in Ruddlesden-Popper-type La2NiO4+delta oxides, the crystal structure, interstitial oxygen formation, electrical conductivity, catalytic activity and chromium tolerance of La2NiO4+delta(LNO)and La2Ni0.9Cu0.1O4+delta(LNCO) are analyzed.
Titulo: Enhanced Electrochemical Performance of Cu-Doped La2NiO4+δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: XRD Rietveld and HT-TEM results confirm that both can be identified as Ruddlesden-Popper-type structures with tetragonal symmetry.
Titulo: Enhanced Electrochemical Performance of Cu-Doped La2NiO4+δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Compared with non-doped LNO, LNCO has less interstitial oxygen, and its electrical conductivity decreases owing to the reduction of the carrier concentration.
Titulo: Enhanced Electrochemical Performance of Cu-Doped La2NiO4+δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The effects on electrode performance are analyzed using symmetric cells, and interface polarization resistance at 800 degrees C is reduced from 2.20 Omega cm(2) to 0.54 Omega cm(2) after Cu-doping.
Titulo: Enhanced Electrochemical Performance of Cu-Doped La2NiO4+δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: Experimental results together with the excellent chromium tolerance confirmed by HT-XRD results demonstrate that Cu-doped LNO can work as a promising chromium-tolerant cathode.
Titulo: Enhanced Electrochemical Performance of Cu-Doped La2NiO4+δ Cathode for Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
